This paper deals with incorporating syntactic information into semantic tasks, which is a common theme in natural language processing (NLP) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on NLP and related topics. The paper also uses multitask learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses neural networks, which are a common tool in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with improving performance on specific tasks, which is a common theme in neural networks and machine learning, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with coreference resolution, which is a task commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) as well as NLP.
